      "type": "prov:Entity",
      "name": "Synthesis of hemolysis modeling prior studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies examining CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps, integrating findings from over a decade of FDA-sponsored benchmark exercises, independent laboratory validations, and inter-laboratory comparison studies. This synthesis consolidates the mechanistic understanding of shear-induced hemolysis, turbulence model selection criteria, and damage accumulation model parameters across more than fifteen published investigations. The synthesis informed the modeling choices, acceptance thresholds, and uncertainty characterization strategy adopted in the present COU assessment."
