    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented justification. Mesh discretization error (GCI 1.8%) and output comparison error (12–19%) both within acceptance criteria. The synthesis of prior studies supporting the modeling approach demonstrates broad literature consensus and strengthens confidence in the model form and parameter selections. Overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the claim that the CFD model identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
